# Embelleze Dashboard · Codex Context

## Identity

Operational dashboard for Instituto Embelleze Trindade commercial team.

- Framework: Astro SSR
- Deploy: Railway direct build from `emb-trind/embelleze-dashboard`
- Domain: `dash-embelleze.up.railway.app`
- Primary goal: give the team a clear, real-time view of leads, funnel, and Meta Ads performance

## Required Reading

Before changing code, read the closest applicable docs:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `CONTEXT.md`
- `CLAUDE.md`
- parent workspace docs when the task touches deploy, workspace, or service boundaries

## Operating Rules

This module is **read-only**. It consumes state — it never writes it.

- Do not write to Postgres, Redis, or any shared state.
- Do not trigger emails, WhatsApp messages, or webhooks.
- All canonical state lives in `embelleze-web`. Never bypass that boundary.
- Every new external integration must live in its own `src/lib/<name>.ts`.
- Do not use jargon in the UI — the audience is the commercial team, not developers.
- Do not hardcode source taxonomy — use the PT-BR taxonomy defined in `CLAUDE.md`.
- Do not use `import.meta.env` for runtime server-side reads — use `process.env`.
- Every new env var must be documented in `SETUP.md` and `.env.example`.
- pnpm only — never npm or yarn.
- Do not touch `.env`, secrets, tokens, or private keys.

## Key Files

- `src/lib/db.ts` — Postgres queries and followup-state reads
- `src/lib/meta.ts` — `fetchMetaInsights()` via Meta Marketing API
- `src/lib/redis.ts` — geo and location reads
- `src/lib/auth.ts` — session cookie handling
- `src/pages/index.astro` — mobile dashboard
- `src/pages/desktop.astro` — desktop bento grid + activity feed
- `src/pages/leads.astro` — contact list
- `src/pages/api/activity.ts` — JSON feed polled every 30s

## Data Sources

| Source | Owner |
|---|---|
| `followup-state.json` | `embelleze-web` (canonical write) |
| Postgres `leads` table | `embelleze-web` |
| Meta Marketing API | `graph.facebook.com` (direct read) |
| Redis geo data | `embelleze-web` via Redis |

## Commands

Use pnpm. The parent workspace also uses pnpm.

```sh
make help
make dev
make check
make build
```

Fallback without Make:

```sh
pnpm check
pnpm build
pnpm dev
```

## Validation

For code changes, run:

```sh
make check
make build
```

For documentation-only or context-only changes, at least inspect the final diff
and confirm no unrelated files were modified.
